{
  "texts": [
    "It shaped the behavior and attitudes of learners.",
    "According to Spolsky (1969), a social context was generally made of the home environment or family, peer group, and the community to which the learner belongs.",
    "Since learners' parents are part of a social environment and culture, their psychology is deeply affected by social values, religion, and culture.",
    "These existing values and social preferences determine their goals and priorities for their children.",
    "Many studies have revealed that children demonstrate their parents\" behaviour and attitudes toward things around them."
  ]
}